div.p:
And I finde it very strange, that when these men will have all that is preached in the word, in the issue left to the free will of man, to beleeve or no, to repent or no, to obey or no; and yet notwithstanding give out, that the word it is, which converts them, brings them to faith, repentance, and obedience;


and yet cavill at our ascribing those effects to the word of God in one kinde of operation, which yet we ascribe solely and immediately to Gods spirit in another kind of operation; 
                        •
                     specially considering that it is Gods word, & not their word; and sent by God in his Spirit, by the ministery of the Prophets, and not sent by them in their Spirits; and it is the meanes whereby Gods Spirit workes, as before I have shewed, and not a meanes, appoynted by them, whereby their Spirit worketh.
